is%20stripes%3F%20In%20his%20third%20outing%20as%20superspy%20Avinash%20Singh%20Rathore%20alias%20Tiger%2C%20Salman%20Khan%2C%20with%20aid%20of%20a%20story%20by%20producer%20Aditya%20Chopra%20and%20a%20screenplay%20from%20Shridhar%20Raghavan%2C%20proves%20that%20there%20is%20always%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20purchase%20from%20the%20spectacle%20of%20an%20irrepressible%20hero%20leaping%20off%20all%20kinds%20of%20perches%20and%20landing%20on%20his%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lead%20actor's%20star%20power%20comes%20in%20handy%2C%20but%20%3Cem%3ETiger%203%3C%2Fem%3E%20(like%20%3Cem%3EPathaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20unlike%20%3Cem%3EWar%3C%2Fem%3E)%20is%20gender-agnostic.%20Katrina%20Kaif%20is%20allowed%20almost%20as%20much%20of%20the%20action%20as%20the%20invincible%20Tiger%2C%20whose%20death-defying%20feats%20return%20in%20the%20third%20instalment%20in%20a%20bigger%20and%20more%20brazen%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20bears%20no%20repetition%20that%20the%20heroine%2C%20herself%20an%20agent%20with%20a%20mean%20streak%2C%20gets%20a%20major%20action%20sequence%20all%20to%20herself%20in%20a%20Turkish%20hamam%20attired%20in%20a%20towel%20as%20she%20goes%20head-to-head%20against%20a%20deadly%20Chinese%20agent%20and%20martial%20arts%20instructor%20(played%20by%20American%20stuntwoman-actress%20Michelle%20Lee).%20The%20two%20deliver%20loads%20of%20cool.%20If%20nothing%20else%2C%20the%20two%20spotless%20towels%20add%20an%20extra%20layer%20to%20the%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20YRF%20spy%20universe%20is%20obviously%20not%20meant%20for%20those%20that%20look%20for%20realistic%2C%20close-to-the-bones%20espionage%20thrillers%20but%20for%20everyone%20else%20(whether%20you%20Salman%20and%20swag)%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20in%20here.%20For%20good%20measure%2C%20the%20villain%20in%20this%20film%20isn't%20just%20another%20scowling%2C%20growling%20Pakistani%20agent.%20He%20gives%20the%20hero%20a%20run%20for%20his%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bad%20guy%20does%20not%20fail%20to%20declare%20his%20intention%20to%20wipe%20India%20off%20the%20face%20of%20the%20earth%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%20only%20to%20be%20expected%20%E2%80%93%20but%20he%20is%20anything%20but%20a%20single-not%20adversarial%20figure%20thanks%20to%20the%20writing%20and%20the%20steady%20performance%20that%20Emraan%20Hashmi%20comes%20up%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20action%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20film%20belongs%20more%20to%20the%20stunt%20doubles%20than%20to%20the%20two%20stars.%20In%20the%20second%2C%20things%20balance%20out%20and%20Salman%20and%20Katrina%20jump%20in%20%E2%80%93%20yes%2C%20jump%20is%20the%20operative%20word%20%E2%80%93%20and%20are%20joined%20by%20another%20superstar%20of%20the%20universe%20returning%20a%20favour%20that%20he%20received%20in%20his%20previous%20film%20of%20the%20thriving%20genre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETiger%203%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20directed%20by%20Maneesh%20Sharma%2C%20takes%20only%20three%20sequences%20to%20spell%20out%20what%20it%20is%20going%20to%20be%20about.%20It%20opens%20with%20Zoya's%20(Katrina%20Kaif)%20origin%20story.%20It%20is%20brief%2C%20to%20the%20point%20and%20plays%20out%20in%20London%20at%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20millennium.%20The%20prelude%20also%20introduces%20a%20character%20that%20is%20destined%20to%20quickly%20acquire%20a%20larger-than-life%20aura%2C%20if%20only%20a%20little%20less%20than%20that%20of%20the%20titular%20hero.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESequence%202%20has%20R%26amp%3BAW%20chief%20Maithili%20Menon%20(Revathy)%20sending%20Tiger%20on%20a%20quick%20rescue%20operation%20aptly%20called%20Mission%20Timepass.%20If%20%E2%80%98timepass'%20is%20what%20%3Cem%3ETiger%203%3C%2Fem%3E%20wants%20to%20be%2C%20it%20succeeds%20in%20achieving%20that%20end%20%E2%80%93%20and%20then%20some.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECut%20to%20the%20next%20sequence.%20The%20man%20that%20Tiger%20has%20been%20charged%20with%20rescuing%20from%20a%20land%20from%20where%20no%20Indian%20agent%20has%20ever%20come%20out%20alive%20insists%20that%20there%20was%20nothing%20%E2%80%98personal'%20in%20his%20act%20of%20firing%20at%20the%20agency's%20go-to%20all-weather%2C%20all-terrain%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20story%20takes%20on%20personal%20proportions%20for%20Tiger%20and%20Zoya%20on%20one%20hand%20and%20a%20former%20ISI%20agent%2C%20Aatish%20Rehman%20(Emraan%20Hashmi)%2C%20on%20the%20other.%20The%20battle%20is%20between%20truth%20and%20half-truth%2C%20between%20betrayal%20and%20redemption%2C%20between%20blackmail%20and%20resistance%2C%20between%20democracy%20and%20dictatorship%2C%20and%20between%20double%20agents%20and%20genuine%20comrades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20noteworthy%20aspect%20of%20%3Cem%3ETiger%203%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20pans%20out%20in%20Istanbul%2C%20St.%20Petersburg%2C%20Vienna%2C%20Islamabad%20and%20a%20high-security%20prison%20in%20a%20mountainous%20part%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20is%20that%20Tiger%2C%20Zoya%20and%20their%20team%20do%20not%20fight%20a%20nation%20as%20a%20whole%20but%20only%20a%20bunch%20of%20renegades%20in%20the%20ISI%20and%20the%20Army%20who%20are%20out%20to%20stage%20a%20coup%20against%20the%20country's%20peacenik%20prime%20minister%2C%20Nasreen%20Irani%20(Simran).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20significant%20reversal%20of%20a%20well-worn%20formula.%20The%20rulers%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20its%20people%20have%20often%20been%20projected%20as%20separate%20entities%20in%20Hindi%20action%20films.%20In%20%3Cem%3ETiger%203%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20distinction%20is%20additionally%20made%20between%20a%20democratically%20elected%20ruler%20and%20rogue%20elements%20within%20the%20nation's%20army%20and%20intelligence%20establishment%20who%20are%20out%20to%20dislodge%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20what%20is%20a%20major%20expansion%20of%20the%20notion%20of%20a%20surgical%20strike%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20crucial%20action%20scenes%20are%20staged%20in%20the%20prime%20ministerial%20enclave%20in%20the%20Pakistani%20capital%20%E2%80%93%20in%20its%20kitchen%2C%20its%20bunker%20and%20its%20stables%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20nation's%20Independence%20Day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20developments%20that%20lead%20Tiger%2C%20his%20wife%20and%20their%20mates%2C%20including%20Rakesh%20Chaurasia%20(Kumud%20Mishra)%20and%20Anand%20Rao%20(Anant%20Vidhaat)%2C%20there%20forms%20the%20crux%20of%20the%20story.%20In%20its%20folds%20are%20plot%20details%20about%20what%20happens%20to%20the%20spy-couple's%20son%2C%20Junior%20(Sartaaj%20Kakkar)%2C%20and%20a%20pregnant%20Pakistani%20agent%2C%20Shaheen%20(Riddhi%20Dogra%20in%20a%20cameo)%2C%20to%20whom%20two%20key%20characters%20are%20directly%20related.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWatching%20%3Cem%3ETiger%203%3C%2Fem%3E%20demands%20a%20willingness%20to%20turn%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20occasional%20lapses%20in%20logic%20and%20the%20monotony%20that%20some%20of%20the%20action%20blocks%20engender%2C%20especially%20when%20they%20overstay%20their%20welcome.%20All%20of%20them%20do%20just%20that%20sooner%20or%20later.%20%3Cem%3ETiger%203%3C%2Fem%3E%20would%20have%20been%20better%20served%20had%20the%20editing%20been%20sharper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20jungle%20that%20Tiger%20inhabits%2C%20the%20laws%20are%20clear.%20Half%20measures%20aren't%20welcome.%20Everything%20that%20this%20espionage%20thriller%20assembles%20is%20multiplied%20by%20three%20at%20the%20very%20least%20and%20delivered%20with%20abandon.%20Take%20it%20or%20lump%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETiger%203%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20the%20sort%20of%20film%20where%20action%20frequently%20overshadows%20acting.%20The%20stunt%20choreographers%2C%20the%20cinematographer%20(Anay%20Goswami)%20and%20the%20VFX%20team%20deserve%20unstinted%20ovation.%20Each%20of%20the%20action%20high%20points%20contribute%20to%20keeping%20the%20film%20galloping%20until%2C%20as%20has%20been%20pointed%20out%20earlier%20in%20this%20review%2C%20they%20are%20in%20danger%20of%20being%20snuffed%20out%20by%20overkill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20technical%20razzmatazz%20that%20the%20film%20rides%20on%20woul